# Documentation
#
# Zensical is the static site generator for project docs (Python autodoc +
# navigation + styling). It is a next-gen successor to MkDocs Material from
# the same author (squidfunk), built on modern tooling. It is still pre-1.0
# — pinning exact versions because the API surface is still moving.
#
# mkdocstrings + mkdocstrings-python provide the Python autodoc directive
# (::: module.path) used on the code-reference pages.
#
# The OpenAPI spec is rendered in the browser by the Scalar standalone
# bundle loaded from jsdelivr (pinned version + SRI hash in docs/api.html).
# Zensical just copies api.html and openapi.json into the build via the
# static-file wiring in mkdocs.yml — no additional plugin needed for it.
zensical==0.0.33
mkdocstrings==1.0.4
mkdocstrings-python==2.0.3

